{"title_page": "Gaurav Chaudhary", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian Tech YouTuber}} \n{{pp-move-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2019}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| channels        = [https://www.youtube.com/c/Technicalguruji Technical Guruji]<br>[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCXsXitjiT_8qPgNEFGPVfBA Gaurav Chaudhary]\n| birth_name      = Gaurav Chaudhary\n| birth_date      = \n| birth_place     = [[Ajmer]], [[Rajasthan]], India\n| education       = \n| religion        = \n| nationality     = Indian<ref>{{cite tweet|number=923768011630166017|user=TechnicalGuruji|title=Pichli photo dekho sir, Indian Passport hai aur iska poora proud hai...Warna ab tak toh kisi aur country ka mil chuka hota...|date=26 October 2017|accessdate=3 September 2019}}</ref>\n| residence       = [[Dubai]], [[United Arab Emirates]]<ref name=\"NewsX\"/>\n| occupation      = Nano Science Researcher<br>[[List of YouTubers|YouTuber]]<br>[[Technology journalism|Tech blogger]]\n| website         = \n| years_active    = 2015\u2013present\n| subscribers     = 15.5 million (Technical Guruji)<ref name=\"Technical Guruji\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCOhHO2ICt0ti9KAh-QHvttQ|title=Technical Guruji|website=YouTube|language=en}}</ref><br />3.17 million (Gaurav Chaudhary)<ref name=\"Gaurav Chaudhary\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCXsXitjiT_8qPgNEFGPVfBA|title=Gaurav Chaudhary|website=YouTube|language=en}}</ref>\n| views           = 1.66 billion (Technical Guruji)<ref name=\"Technical Guruji\"/><br />137.3&nbsp;million (Gaurav Chaudhary)<ref name=\"Gaurav Chaudhary\"/>\n| associated_acts = Sharmaji Technical<br>GeekyRanjit<br>Nikhil Sharma (Mumbiker Nikhil)<br>Amit Bhawani (PhoneRadar)\n| silver_button   = yes\n| silver_year     = 2016 (Technical Guruji)<br />2018 (Gaurav Choudhary)\n| gold_button     = yes\n| gold_year       = 2017 (Technical Guruji)<br />2018 (Gaurav Chaudhary)\n| diamond_button  = Yes\n| diamond_year    = 2018 (Technical Guruji)\n| stats_update    = 16 March 2020\n}}\n\n'''Gaurav Chaudhary''', known professionally as '''Technical Guruji''', is an Indian [[YouTube personality]] based in Dubai. Chaudhary is notable for producing YouTube videos concerning technology in [[Hindi]]. As of March 2020, Gaurav Chaudhary and the Technical Guruji channel combined has accrued over 18 million subscribers on the platform.<ref name=\"socialblade\">{{Cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/top/category/tech|title=Top 250 YouTubers tech Channels \u2013 Socialblade YouTube Stats {{!}} YouTube Statistics|website=socialblade.com}}</ref><ref name=\"Technical Guruji\"/><ref name=\"Gaurav Chaudhary\"/> He has been featured in 30 under 30 [[Forbes India|Forbes]] list.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbesindia.com/lists/30-under-30-2020/1829/all|title=Forbes India 30 Under 30 2020|work=[[Forbes India]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.businessinsider.in/thelife/personalities/news/gaurav-chaudhary-from-a-security-engineer-to-forbes-30-under-30-as-technical-guruji-from-india/articleshow/73958471.cms|title=The story of Technical Guruji who talked his way to the Forbes India 30 under 30 list - in Hindi|first=Rounak |last=Jain|date=7 February 2020|work=[[Business Insider]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and career==\nChaudhary was born in [[Ajmer]], [[Rajasthan]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bhatt |first1=Shephali |title=Desi dreams: The rise of Indian internet content creators abroad |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/people/desi-dreams-the-rise-of-indian-internet-content-creators-abroad/articleshow/71777206.cms |accessdate=15 January 2020 |work=The Economic Times |date=3 November 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"BS\">{{cite news |title=World's largest Hindi tech channel 'Technical Guruji' hits 13mn subscribers |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/world-s-largest-hindi-tech-channel-technical-guruji-hits-13mn-subscribers-119062000953_1.html |accessdate=15 January 2020 |work=[[Business Standard]] |agency=[[Asian News International|ANI]] |date=20 June 2019 |archiveurl=http://archive.today/MPGVd |archivedate=3 July 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> He studied at a [[Kendriya Vidyalaya|Kendriya Vidyalaya school]]. In 2012 he moved to [[Dubai]] to pursue a degree in [[microelectronics]] at [[Birla Institute of Technology and Science, Pilani \u2013 Dubai Campus|BITS Pilani, Dubai Campus]]. In Dubai, he received a certification to work with security systems from the Dubai police, but also started a YouTube channel besides his work. Chaudhary launched his Technical Guruji channel in October 2015, primarily posting advice and product reviews. The channel grew quickly, and in 2017 Chaudhary created a second channel dedicated to producing content about his personal life.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.techradar.com/news/youtube-india-fanfest-2018-is-going-to-be-a-multi-city-event-this-year|title=YouTube India Fanfest 2018 is going to be a multi-city event this year|work=TechRadar|access-date=22 September 2018|language=EN-GB}}</ref>\n\nChaudhary's Technical Guruji channel continued its rapid growth. In September 2018, Technical Guruji was ranked as the 9th most subscribed to tech YouTube channel.<ref name=\"socialblade\"/> In November 2018, it was reported that Chaudhary was the first tech YouTuber to accrue more than 10 million subscribers.<ref name=\"NewsX\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsx.com/science-and-technology/technical-guruji-becomes-worlds-first-youtube-channel-with-10-million-subscribers|title=Technical Guruji becomes world's first tech YouTube channel with 10 million subscribers|last=P|first=Manish|last2=Says|first2=Ey|date=15 November 2018|website=NewsX|language=en|access-date=10 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nChaudhary participated in [[YouTube Rewind]] 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bgr.in/news/youtube-rewind-2018-more-downvotes-than-upvotes-will-smith-fortnite-technical-guruji-reddit-memes/|title=YouTube Rewind 2018 video out now; gets more downvotes than upvotes|last=Staff|date=7 December 2018|website=BGR India|language=en-US|access-date=10 December 2018}}</ref> and 2019.\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chaudhary, Gaurav}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Birla Institute of Technology and Science alumni]]\n[[Category:Technical YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Technology blogs]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:People from Dubai]]\n[[Category:People from Ajmer]]\n[[Category:YouTube Diamond Play Button recipients]]\n[[Category:YouTube Gold Play Button recipients]]\n\n\n{{India-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian Tech YouTuber}} \n{{pp-move-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2019}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| channels        = [https://www.youtube.com/c/Technicalguruji Technical Guruji]<br>[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCXsXitjiT_8qPgNEFGPVfBA Gaurav Chaudhary]\n| birth_name      = Gaurav Chaudhary\n| birth_date      = \n| birth_place     = [[Ajmer]], [[Rajasthan]], India\n| education       = \n| religion        = \n| nationality     = Indian<ref>{{cite tweet|number=923768011630166017|user=TechnicalGuruji|title=Pichli photo dekho sir, Indian Passport hai aur iska poora proud hai...Warna ab tak toh kisi aur country ka mil chuka hota...|date=26 October 2017|accessdate=3 September 2019}}</ref>\n| residence       = [[Dubai]], [[United Arab Emirates]]<ref name=\"NewsX\"/>\n| occupation      = Nano Science Researcher<br>[[List of YouTubers|YouTuber]]<br>[[Technology journalism|Tech blogger]]\n| website         = \n| years_active    = 2015\u2013present\n| subscribers     = 15.5 million (Technical Guruji)<ref name=\"Technical Guruji\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCOhHO2ICt0ti9KAh-QHvttQ|title=Technical Guruji|website=YouTube|language=en}}</ref><br />3.17 million (Gaurav Chaudhary)<ref name=\"Gaurav Chaudhary\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCXsXitjiT_8qPgNEFGPVfBA|title=Gaurav Chaudhary|website=YouTube|language=en}}</ref>\n| views           = 1.66 billion (Technical Guruji)<ref name=\"Technical Guruji\"/><br />137.3&nbsp;million (Gaurav Chaudhary)<ref name=\"Gaurav Chaudhary\"/>\n| associated_acts = Sharmaji Technical<br>GeekyRanjit<br>Nikhil Sharma (Mumbiker Nikhil)<br>Amit Bhawani (PhoneRadar)\n| silver_button   = yes\n| silver_year     = 2016 (Technical Guruji)<br />2018 (Gaurav Choudhary)\n| gold_button     = yes\n| gold_year       = 2017 (Technical Guruji)<br />2018 (Gaurav Chaudhary)\n| diamond_button  = Yes\n| diamond_year    = 2018 (Technical Guruji)\n| stats_update    = 16 March 2020\n}}\n\n'''Gaurav Chaudhary''', known professionally as '''Technical Guruji''', is an Indian [[YouTube personality]] based in Dubai. Chaudhary is notable for producing YouTube videos concerning technology in [[Hindi]]. As of March 2020, Gaurav Chaudhary and the Technical Guruji channel combined has accrued over 18 million subscribers on the platform.<ref name=\"socialblade\">{{Cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/top/category/tech|title=Top 250 YouTubers tech Channels \u2013 Socialblade YouTube Stats {{!}} YouTube Statistics|website=socialblade.com}}</ref><ref name=\"Technical Guruji\"/><ref name=\"Gaurav Chaudhary\"/> He has been featured in 30 under 30 [[Forbes India|Forbes]] list.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbesindia.com/lists/30-under-30-2020/1829/all|title=Forbes India 30 Under 30 2020|work=[[Forbes India]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.businessinsider.in/thelife/personalities/news/gaurav-chaudhary-from-a-security-engineer-to-forbes-30-under-30-as-technical-guruji-from-india/articleshow/73958471.cms|title=The story of Technical Guruji who talked his way to the Forbes India 30 under 30 list - in Hindi|first=Rounak |last=Jain|date=7 February 2020|work=[[Business Insider]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and career==\nChaudhary was born in [[Ajmer]], [[Rajasthan]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bhatt |first1=Shephali |title=Desi dreams: The rise of Indian internet content creators abroad |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/people/desi-dreams-the-rise-of-indian-internet-content-creators-abroad/articleshow/71777206.cms |accessdate=15 January 2020 |work=The Economic Times |date=3 November 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"BS\">{{cite news |title=World's largest Hindi tech channel 'Technical Guruji' hits 13mn subscribers |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/world-s-largest-hindi-tech-channel-technical-guruji-hits-13mn-subscribers-119062000953_1.html |accessdate=15 January 2020 |work=[[Business Standard]] |agency=[[Asian News International|ANI]] |date=20 June 2019 |archiveurl=http://archive.today/MPGVd |archivedate=3 July 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> He studied at a [[Kendriya Vidyalaya|Kendriya Vidyalaya school]]. In 2012 he moved to [[Dubai]] to pursue a degree in [[microelectronics]] at [[Birla Institute of Technology and Science, Pilani \u2013 Dubai Campus|BITS Pilani, Dubai Campus]]. In Dubai, he received a certification to work with security systems from the Dubai police, but also started a YouTube channel besides his work. Chaudhary launched his Technical Guruji channel in October 2015, primarily posting advice and product reviews. The channel grew quickly, and in 2017 Chaudhary created a second channel dedicated to producing content about his personal life.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.techradar.com/news/youtube-india-fanfest-2018-is-going-to-be-a-multi-city-event-this-year|title=YouTube India Fanfest 2018 is going to be a multi-city event this year|work=TechRadar|access-date=22 September 2018|language=EN-GB}}</ref>\n\nChaudhary's Technical Guruji channel continued its rapid growth. In September 2018, Technical Guruji was ranked as the 9th most subscribed to tech YouTube channel.<ref name=\"socialblade\"/> In November 2018, it was reported that Chaudhary was the first tech YouTuber to accrue more than 10 million subscribers.<ref name=\"NewsX\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsx.com/science-and-technology/technical-guruji-becomes-worlds-first-youtube-channel-with-10-million-subscribers|title=Technical Guruji becomes world's first tech YouTube channel with 10 million subscribers|last=P|first=Manish|last2=Says|first2=Ey|date=15 November 2018|website=NewsX|language=en|access-date=10 December 2018}}</ref>[[pedialedge]]\n\nChaudhary participated in [[YouTube Rewind]] 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bgr.in/news/youtube-rewind-2018-more-downvotes-than-upvotes-will-smith-fortnite-technical-guruji-reddit-memes/|title=YouTube Rewind 2018 video out now; gets more downvotes than upvotes|last=Staff|date=7 December 2018|website=BGR India|language=en-US|access-date=10 December 2018}}</ref> and 2019.\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chaudhary, Gaurav}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Birla Institute of Technology and Science alumni]]\n[[Category:Technical YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Technology blogs]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:People from Dubai]]\n[[Category:People from Ajmer]]\n[[Category:YouTube Diamond Play Button recipients]]\n[[Category:YouTube Gold Play Button recipients]]\n\n\n{{India-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Pedialedge", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaurav_Chaudhary"}
{"title_page": "Hwamyeong-dong", "text_new": "{{Infobox Korean name|\nhangul=\ud654\uba85\ub3d9|\nhanja=\u83ef\u660e\u6d1e|\nrr=Hwamyeong-dong|\nmr=Hwamy\u014fng-dong|\n}}\n\n'''Hwamyeong''' is a region in [[Buk-gu (Busan)|Buk-gu]], northern [[Busan]], [[South Korea]].  It is situated along the east bank of the [[Nakdong River]], and since 2003 has been divided into three ''[[Subdivisions of South Korea|dong]]'', Hwamyeong 1, 2, and 3-dong.  The total area of the three ''dong'' is approximately {{convert|12|km\u00b2|0|abbr=on}}. It was made to serve the role of [[commuter town]] of Busan,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.joins.com/article/4099431|title=\ubd80\uc0b0 \ud654\uba85\ub3d9 '\uc0c8 \ubca0\ub4dc\ud0c0\uc6b4' \ubd80\uc0c1, Pusan Hwamyeon-dong arise as 'New Bed Town'|last=\uc9c0\uba74\ubcf4\uae30|first=\uc785\ub825 2001 07 03 00:00 {{!}} \uc885\ud569 25\uba74|date=2001-07-03|website=\uc911\uc559\uc77c\ubcf4|language=ko|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> and it is home to about 99,000 people on the date of February 2020.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.bsbukgu.go.kr/index.bsbukgu?menuCd=DOM_000000119005001001|title=( \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130\uc18c\uac1c ) {{!}} \uc6b0\ub9ac\ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130 {{!}} \ud654\uba851\ub3d9 {{!}} \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130 {{!}} \ubd81\uad6c \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130|website=www.bsbukgu.go.kr|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bsbukgu.go.kr/index.bsbukgu?menuCd=DOM_000000119006001001|title=( \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130\uc18c\uac1c ) {{!}} \uc6b0\ub9ac\ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130 {{!}} \ud654\uba852\ub3d9 {{!}} \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130 {{!}} \ubd81\uad6c \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130|website=www.bsbukgu.go.kr|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bsbukgu.go.kr/index.bsbukgu?menuCd=DOM_000000119007001001|title=( \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130\uc18c\uac1c ) {{!}} \uc6b0\ub9ac\ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130 {{!}} \ud654\uba853\ub3d9 {{!}} \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130 {{!}} \ubd81\uad6c \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130|website=www.bsbukgu.go.kr|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n== Name ==\nThe name Hwamyeong, has many view of where it is derived from. The most reliable theory is that Mt. Geumjung, which is the mountain surrounds Hwamyeong, has another name, Mt. Hwa. It is originated from being called an ideal or bright place near Mt. Hwa, and the Chinese letter for ideal is pronounce 'myeong' in Korean, when put together, it becomes 'Hwamyeong'.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://library.bsbukgu.go.kr/html/06story/story/0503.php#%EC%84%9C%EC%9E%A5|title=\ubd81\uad6c\ud5a5\ud1a0\uc9c0 - \uc9c0\uba85 \uc720\ub798 - \ud654\uba85\ub3d9. Buk-gu land map - name origin - Hwamyeong-dong|last=|first=|date=|website=library.bsbukgu.go.kr|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> Second theory is that the place's original name was ''Hwe-Bulgi'', which means 'bright sun' or 'red sun'.<ref name=\":0\" /> The sun was interpreted as shining, and the adjective was interpreted as bright with the Chinese character. So the current meaning of name is 'brightly shining'. It was first attached to the region in 1914, during the [[Korea under Japanese rule|period of Japanese rule]].  At that time it was Hwamyeong-ri, a subdivision of [[Gupo]]-myeon.  In 1963, it became a ''dong'', part of [[Busanjin-gu]].  In 1978, it was transferred to Buk-gu, which it remained a unitary part of until its division in 2003.\n\nHwamyeong Station lies on the [[Gyeongbu Line]], and is served by several [[Mugunghwa-ho]] and [[Tonggeun]] trains daily.  A [[water purification]] plant is located in Hwamyeong, providing a substantial portion of Busan's drinking water.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Korea-related topics]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://hwamyeong1.busan.go.kr/ Hwamyeong 1-dong Office, in Korean]{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n*[http://hwamyeong2.busan.go.kr/ Hwamyeong 2-dong Office, in Korean]{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n*[http://hwamyeong3.busan.go.kr/ Hwamyeong 3-dong Office, in Korean]{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{coord missing|South Korea}}\n\n[[Category:Buk District, Busan]]\n[[Category:Neighbourhoods in Busan]]\n<references />\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Korean name|\nhangul=\ud654\uba85\ub3d9|\nhanja=\u83ef\u660e\u6d1e|\nrr=Hwamyeong-dong|\nmr=Hwamy\u014fng-dong|\n}}\n\n'''Hwamyeong''' is a region in [[Buk-gu (Busan)|Buk-gu]], northern [[Busan]], [[South Korea]].  It is situated along the east bank of the [[Nakdong River]], and since 2003 has been divided into three ''[[Subdivisions of South Korea|dong]]'', Hwamyeong 1, 2, and 3-dong.  The total area of the three ''dong'' is approximately {{convert|12|km\u00b2|0|abbr=on}}. It was made to serve the role of [[commuter town]] of Busan,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.joins.com/article/4099431|title=\ubd80\uc0b0 \ud654\uba85\ub3d9 '\uc0c8 \ubca0\ub4dc\ud0c0\uc6b4' \ubd80\uc0c1, Pusan Hwamyeon-dong arise as 'New Bed Town'|last=\uc9c0\uba74\ubcf4\uae30|first=\uc785\ub825 2001 07 03 00:00 {{!}} \uc885\ud569 25\uba74|date=2001-07-03|website=\uc911\uc559\uc77c\ubcf4|language=ko|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> and it is home to about 99,000 people on the date of February 2020.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.bsbukgu.go.kr/index.bsbukgu?menuCd=DOM_000000119005001001|title=( \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130\uc18c\uac1c ) {{!}} \uc6b0\ub9ac\ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130 {{!}} \ud654\uba851\ub3d9 {{!}} \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130 {{!}} \ubd81\uad6c \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130|website=www.bsbukgu.go.kr|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bsbukgu.go.kr/index.bsbukgu?menuCd=DOM_000000119006001001|title=( \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130\uc18c\uac1c ) {{!}} \uc6b0\ub9ac\ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130 {{!}} \ud654\uba852\ub3d9 {{!}} \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130 {{!}} \ubd81\uad6c \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130|website=www.bsbukgu.go.kr|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bsbukgu.go.kr/index.bsbukgu?menuCd=DOM_000000119007001001|title=( \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130\uc18c\uac1c ) {{!}} \uc6b0\ub9ac\ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130 {{!}} \ud654\uba853\ub3d9 {{!}} \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130 {{!}} \ubd81\uad6c \ub3d9\ud589\uc815\ubcf5\uc9c0\uc13c\ud130|website=www.bsbukgu.go.kr|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\nThe name Hwamyeong, has many view of where it is derived from. The most reliable theory is that Mt. Geumjung, which is the mountain surrounds Hwamyeong, has another name, Mt. Hwa. It is originated from being called an ideal or bright place near Mt. Hwa, and the Chinese letter for ideal is pronounce 'myeong' in Korean, when put together, it becomes 'Hwamyeong'.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://library.bsbukgu.go.kr/html/06story/story/0503.php#%EC%84%9C%EC%9E%A5|title=\ubd81\uad6c\ud5a5\ud1a0\uc9c0 - \uc9c0\uba85 \uc720\ub798 - \ud654\uba85\ub3d9. Buk-gu land map - name origin - Hwamyeong-dong|last=|first=|date=|website=library.bsbukgu.go.kr|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> Second theory is that the place's original name was ''Hwe-Bulgi'', which means 'bright sun' or 'red sun'.<ref name=\":0\" /> The sun was interpreted as shining, and the adjective was interpreted as bright with the Chinese character. So the current meaning of name is 'brightly shining'. It was first attached to the region in 1914, during the [[Korea under Japanese rule|period of Japanese rule]].  At that time it was Hwamyeong-ri, a subdivision of [[Gupo]]-myeon.  In 1963, it became a ''dong'', part of [[Busanjin-gu]].  In 1978, it was transferred to Buk-gu, which it remained a unitary part of until its division in 2003.\n\nHwamyeong Station lies on the [[Gyeongbu Line]], and is served by several [[Mugunghwa-ho]] and [[Tonggeun]] trains daily.  A [[water purification]] plant is located in Hwamyeong, providing a substantial portion of Busan's drinking water.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Korea-related topics]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://hwamyeong1.busan.go.kr/ Hwamyeong 1-dong Office, in Korean]{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n*[http://hwamyeong2.busan.go.kr/ Hwamyeong 2-dong Office, in Korean]{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n*[http://hwamyeong3.busan.go.kr/ Hwamyeong 3-dong Office, in Korean]{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{coord missing|South Korea}}\n\n[[Category:Buk District, Busan]]\n[[Category:Neighbourhoods in Busan]]\n<references />\n", "name_user": "GyongminM", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hwamyeong-dong"}
